PyTraffic – Installation
========================

Requirements
------------
  * Python 3.8 or newer
  * GTK 3 with Python bindings: PyGObject (python3-gi / python-gobject)
  * GStreamer 1.x with Python bindings (python3-gst-1.0 / gst-python)
    and plugins: gst-plugins-base, gst-plugins-good (OGG/Vorbis playback)
  * GCC toolchain (to build the _hint C extension)

On Fedora/RHEL:
    sudo dnf install python3-gobject gtk3 \
                     python3-gstreamer1 gstreamer1-plugins-good \
                     gcc python3-devel

On Debian/Ubuntu:
    sudo apt install python3-gi python3-gi-cairo gir1.2-gtk-3.0 \
                     python3-gst-1.0 gir1.2-gstreamer-1.0 \
                     gstreamer1.0-plugins-good gstreamer1.0-plugins-base \
                     gcc python3-dev


Running directly from the source checkout (development)
-------------------------------------------------------
Build the _hint C extension in-place and launch the game:

    make          # builds _hint.cpython-<ver>-<arch>.so in the project root
    make run      # build + launch

Or equivalently:

    python setup.py build_ext --inplace
    python Main.py

The Makefile also provides:

    make clean        # remove build/ artefacts (keeps the .so)
    make distclean    # full clean including the compiled extension


Installing system-wide or into a virtual environment (pip)
----------------------------------------------------------
    pip install .                # into the active environment
    pip install --user .         # into ~/.local  (no root needed)

After installation the game is launched with:

    pytraffic

Data files (themes, music, UI, …) are installed under
<prefix>/share/pytraffic/ and the pytraffic script sets the working
directory there automatically.


Uninstalling
------------
    pip uninstall pytraffic
